<p>
<seg id=1> Israeli Prime Minister Netaneyahu appointed Sharon, the top hardliner in the Israeli government, to be Foreign Minister. </seg>
<seg id=2> This appointment came just at the time when a temporary peace agreement was reached by the leaders of Israel and Palestine before the summit meeting in USA. </seg>
<seg id=3> According to the agreement, Israel is to give away more land on the west bank of Jordan to the Palestinians. </seg>
<seg id=4> Sharon firmly insists on establishing Jewish settlements on the west bank of Jordan River and is against making any compromise on the issue of army withdrawal. </seg>
</p>
